      "content": "I think I see. So the visual complexity really comes down to which node the phrase is branching from. When you're drawing these out, do you find that the more complex trees—the ones with all those extra adjunct branches and deep nesting—are harder for students to actually parse visually? It feels like the \"shape\" of the tree can get pretty messy when you have a lot of modifiers.",
